cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with unsupervised learning of visual representations from video data using deep neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning for action recognition (cs.AI) and object recognition (cs.MM) tasks, and the use of multi-stream temporal processing architectures (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
